Definitions:
> Variables - holds a certain type of value either integer, strings or boolean in the javascript program.
> Strings - this are the values which enclosed in double quotes upon declaration in variables.
> Functions (arguments, return) - block of codes that can be called anytime in the javascript program [re-usable block of codes]. 
> if statements - conditional statement that evaluates the condition that proceeds to return either true or false.
> Boolean values (true, false) - this are the values that used in conditional statemet to give an output either true or false.
